30:05.919 --> 30:06.520
But French are better.

30:07.006 --> 30:26.682
So there aren't too many really great copies of science books.

30:26.702 --> 30:27.684
They're not terribly interesting from collecting.

30:27.704 --> 30:28.245
And Freud's are not either.

30:28.265 --> 30:29.647
All of Freud's books were published in the original printed records.

30:29.667 --> 30:31.090
So they're almost all re-bound, you see.

30:31.508 --> 30:42.821
But they were used, as you point out, too.

30:42.841 --> 30:52.552
Well, they were used, and not only that, there were 600 copies only, and some of them were cult, maybe, and so forth.

30:52.572 --> 30:57.938
But the important thing is that they were printed on rather mediocre paper, and most 19th century German books are not that, especially in science.

30:58.323 --> 31:01.567
I'm sure there are exceptions, you know, in the art area and so forth.

31:02.248 --> 31:06.233
So getting good copies is a really difficult thing.

