31:58.879 --> 32:02.286
Freud has come under some criticism recently.

32:02.306 --> 32:04.150
Always been.

32:04.170 --> 32:15.171
Do you still feel that most of his material, and I'm talking as a strict layman now, I'm just curious, but he has been, how do you, that's a general question.

32:15.231 --> 32:16.153
You know, my opinion is very simple.

32:16.910 --> 32:27.622
History will establish it.

32:27.642 --> 32:31.766
I don't have to worry about it.

32:31.786 --> 32:40.055
I think I've accepted what he presented as a valid and useful, but that doesn't mean that I don't think he was a crook, and some of the people are willing to say.

32:40.075 --> 32:42.398
I think he did what he thought was, he gave what he thought was understandable and meaningful.

32:42.418 --> 32:45.381
But in any science, we don't think he had the last word, and so I'm not terribly worried about it.

32:45.850 --> 33:02.195
But honestly, I mean, I think that whatever happens a hundred years from now, it would depend on who else is able to evaluate.

33:02.215 --> 33:04.919
Right now, you know, this is nitpicking, it's hard not concerned.

33:05.080 --> 33:10.588
So, okay, maybe he didn't say this exactly the way his purpose of doing it, like one of the attacks on his case histories, he wasn't honest or something like that.

33:10.608 --> 33:11.790
Well, he used them to illustrate some of his ideas.

33:12.125 --> 33:22.376
And maybe you may have exaggerated, but that's not the point.

33:22.396 --> 33:24.619
Most of us found these examples useful.

33:24.799 --> 33:31.106
So, but to assume that, you know, they're the last word is nonsensical.

33:31.126 --> 33:33.769
I don't feel terribly involved.

33:33.789 --> 33:35.871
And most of these people that take issue have a history of being

33:36.273 --> 33:38.015
critical for Freud.

33:38.175 --> 33:43.240
I mean, look, there's an article on it in the New York Times somewhere.

33:43.261 --> 33:45.022
There was some professor at MIT.

33:45.042 --> 33:48.646
I think I saw that piece I'm thinking about.

33:48.666 --> 33:49.928
Yeah, I think so.

33:50.328 --> 33:56.795
And his greatest supporter was a professor here who we know is already critical.

33:57.356 --> 33:57.476
He is.

33:57.496 --> 34:03.242
So there's no reason why that shouldn't occur, you know, if you have different kinds of views.

34:03.931 --> 34:17.989
The most important aspect is the way the judges will be made by people who do the work.

34:18.911 --> 34:25.219
They can't be made by people who are historians or writers.

34:25.239 --> 34:33.870
